Sentencas: The residual stress of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (MT-SOFC) was investigated by a twodimensional axisymmetric model.
Titulo: Effect of Component Thickness and Anode Composition on the Residual Stress of Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The mechanical stability of anode, electrolyte and cathode was evaluated with the consideration of Ni volume fraction and layer thickness.
Titulo: Effect of Component Thickness and Anode Composition on the Residual Stress of Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The results reveal that the high Ni volume fraction in anode is detrimental to the mechanical stability of MT-SOFC: when the Ni volume fraction is more than 50% in solid, it will be hard to keep the integrity of every cell layer within a reasonable thickness range.
Titulo: Effect of Component Thickness and Anode Composition on the Residual Stress of Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In order to facilitate the cell design, a minimum anode thickness formula for safe and durable operation was proposed as a function of the Ni volume fraction, electrolyte thickness and cathode thickness.
Titulo: Effect of Component Thickness and Anode Composition on the Residual Stress of Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: This work simultaneously considered both the Ni volume fraction and layer thickness, which provided a more realistic estimation about MT-SOFC mechanical stability.
Titulo: Effect of Component Thickness and Anode Composition on the Residual Stress of Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
